en.text:
It’s not a good idea to create this effect manually. It’s better to use a CSS code in the <style> tag to accomplish this. The code looks like this:

<style>

body {

font-family: serif;

font-size: 18px;

line-height: 21px;

color: #FFF;

font-weight: bold;

}

.boldText {

font-weight: bold;

}

</style>

<div class="boldText">Here is bold text</div>

You could also use tags in HTML like this:

<b>Here is bold text</b>

But this is slightly less flexible and will only work if you know the exact HTML code to use for your situation.

